records.addlTxt: Final pre-trial on August 8, 2022 at 10:00 am.

2:46 PM Defendant Chelsae R Gallup in court.  Attorney Michael Daniel Zell in court for Chelsae R Gallup.  Attorney Daniel McGrath in court for State of Wisconsin. Motion to suppress.  Deputy Downs is sworn as witness and testifies to the facts.  Testifies to making contacts with a vehicle that was in the ditch after being called by a towing company.  Testifies to the defendant being in the drivers seat of the vehicle.  Witness identifies the defendant and Court recognizes.  Witness recognized an odor of marijuana coming from the vehicle.  Testifies that the defendant said they had not smoked anything, the passenger also said they had not smoked anything.  Testifies he was wearing a body camera that day.  State plays video in Court and that is reviewed.  Video is marked exhibit 1.  Attorney Zell cross examines  Body camera video, exhibit 1 is played  Witness reviews who was at the scene and the weather conditions at the scene.   Testifies to his training regarding his questioning of the defendant.  Redirect Attorney McGrath.  Attorney McGrath argues.  Attorney Zell makes his argument.  Court finds probable cause for the search, motion to suppress is denied.
Final pre-trial scheduled for August 5, 2022 at 10:00 am.

02:57 PM Defendant Chelsae R Gallup in court with attorney Michael Daniel Zell.  Matthew Steven McElroy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Christopher Downs is sworn as a witness and questioned by Attorney Oswald. He is a deputy with the Wood County Sheriff's Department. On 1/22/22, he responded to a vehicle crash on Highway 73. The defendant was the driver of the vehicle. The witness identifies the defendant in the courtroom. Defendant stated that it was her vehicle. A search was done and he found a bindle with a white powdery substance and a blue container container with a powdery substance in a compartment in the front seat. He also found what appeared to be THC. A passenger was also in the vehicle. The defendant denied using drugs, but later admitted to smoking marijuana. He tested the substance and it tested positive for the presence of Fentanyl. Attorney Zell cross-examines witness.
Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and the defendant committed it. Not guilty plea. Bond is continued.  Final pre-trial scheduled for April 22, 2022 at 11:00 am.
